 {"id":"bd-adke","title":"ffs-fuse ioctl_trace_path probe does synchronous unbuffered file I/O per ioctl","description":"In crates/ffs-fuse/src/lib.rs, record_ioctl_probe opens, appends, and writes to ioctl_trace_path synchronously on every ioctl request. If enabled, this will block the FUSE dispatcher thread and perform terribly under load. It should at least use a buffered writer or an async channel if used beyond simple E2E tests.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T16:51:44.249493094Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-19T21:58:12.855457161Z","closed_at":"2026-04-19T21:58:12.852694301Z","close_reason":"Replaced Mutex<BufWriter<File>> with bounded mpsc::sync_channel + dedicated ffs-ioctl-trace writer thread. record() is now a non-blocking try_send with audited drop counter; flush_sync() provides deterministic happens-before barrier for tests. New 8-thread concurrency test passes; 184/184 ffs-fuse tests green; clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings clean. sha=19f61cf","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
